{
  "texts": [
    "[231] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" refers to the tendency of LLMs to hallucinate facts and fabricate information. 213 Nori et al.",
    "[232] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to erroneous generations by ChatGPT. 214 Li et al.",
    "[233] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" occurs when LLMs generate content that conflicts with the source or cannot be verified by factual knowledge. 215 Zhao et al.",
    "[234] 2023 Large Language Model \"Intrinsic hallucination\" refers to the generated information in conflict with the existing source.",
    "\"Extrinsic hallucination\" refers to the generated information that cannot be verified by the available source. 216 Adlakha et al."
  ]
}